jScL6I7zU3J_733kXmfhcLnMwhVqU4zAgQhdQRN3RMQgZ7wq__89Q9slG-w2nc5RRCYyi4abyO6=
1YNoZ6MYlaU3PuoPf4F9WU7_GGbCslKkgK0yu9_jqWpVa0gZ6knFxrisjJb5VVw ) ; instead=
 of having to choose a model and provision hardware independently, you can =
simply use an API. Llama is the first model available, but there will be mo=
re coming soon.

This, ultimately, is the real Microsoft hedge to OpenAI. Yes, the company i=
s pushing all out to have a fully integrated stack from silicon to user-fac=
ing applications, with OpenAI as the connective tissue in the middle; this =
not only offers the potential for differentiation in terms of performance, =
but more importantly and sustainably an advantage in cost, both because it =
has access to OpenAI=E2=80=99s models but also in terms of infrastructure. =
If it all goes sideways, though, then the company=E2=80=99s traditional pla=
tform model will be the fallback; it will also be relatively undifferentiat=
ed relative to something like AWS, with similar competitive dynamics to the=
 pre-AI cloud. Given that, you can see why Nadella is willing to be quite f=
lexible to ensure that the OpenAI situation is resolved in a manner favorab=
le to Microsoft.

